Singer David ‘Davido’ Adeleke and Austin ‘Jayjay’ Okocha were some of the leading Africans in sport and music to present an award at the 2022 CAF awards. While Davido, alongside Emmanuel Adebayor, presented the award for young female footballer of the year to Ghana’s Evelyn Badu, Okocha presented the award for goal of the year to Papa Ousma Sacho.   Okonjo-Iweala advises Nigeria on WTO fisheries cash     Tiwa Savage performs at 2022 CAF awards     ASUU strike: Students, parents in dilemma over rent renewal   Davido joined eminent sports personalities and dignitaries in Rabat, Morocco for the 2022 edition of the major African sporting event. This is coming a few days after the singer joined his uncle and Osun Governor-elect Ademola Adeleke for the election.